caption: Love the presentation six in the  box... Loaded with sugar & butter. OMG, these chocolate chip cookies are like an overloaded sugared mixture. Looks pleasing delicious homemade oatmeal cookies. But it was quite the opposite....Easily crumble into little pieces was dried-up. These large oversize cookies were too greasy and tough at the edge led me to believe they were fried in oil not bake. So disappointed.... Make sure you buy water, you will certainly need it.

The place is clean, I had almost every cookie. They are large and in charge. Great, amazing, wonderful cookies. I'm not being dramatic... very good! The kisses are good they are made with meringue and are chocolate coated. Taste great with any coffee on their menu. A must stop if you're at or in the area of Dekalb Market  Couldn't post my video but some screenshots

The decor and arrangement of The Flo is adorable and eye-catching. We randomly decided to give it a try when we visited Dekalb Market since the dessert display looked amazingly attractive.  We had Reese kisses (peanut butter flavored) and black & white cookie (a combination of original and chocolate chip). The kisses is a type of dessert from Europe which is made of creamy and dense meringue inside coated with a thin layer of chocolate. However, we didn’t like the melted-in-mouth but greasy texture of meringue.  The black & white cookie was amazingly great. It was a smart idea to have 2 flavors and you won’t have too much at one time. Their cookie was huge and perfect, we felt satisfied to share with 2 people.

At the Union Square Holiday Market, out of a box of 6, 3 of them were not at all fresh! Instead of the Italian meringue being soft & creamy as the others were, they were dry & chewy. Unethical to be selling stale stuff at these prices! Too bad — i expected better.
